{"TopicId":135344,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"What would be humanity\u0026#039;s likeliest demise?","CreatedByName":"Atlas2342","CreatedById":155194,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-30T14:10:44Z","PageNum":6,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"fredinno","CreatedById":143381,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-08T16:51:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222502144\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022135344\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221460117490\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPeople already don\u0027t want offspring\u00A0producing sex. Birth control has become pretty common. But there are\u00A0less hormonal ways of doing that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Income_and_fertility#Fertility_J-curve\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Income_and_fertility#Fertility_J-curve\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022TFR_HDI.PNG\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/4b/TFR_HDI.PNG\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMany scolars think there is a J-curve in birth rates, as people\u0027s lives get easier- which is shown in the graph above. It also makes sense, if people don\u0027t have to work as much, they can take care of more children.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}